The series of Precalculus books by C. Stitz and J. Zeager preapare the students for a subsequent course in Calculus. They cover Algebra, Exponential and Logarithmic Functions, Conic Sections, Matrices and Trigonometry.

This book presented as an Appendix to the Precalculus material, covers the pre-requisites that the student should be familiar before starting on the main material which will be published soon as separate books.

This book itself, covers Basic Set theory, Cartesian Plane and Graphing Lines, Linear Equations in Two Unknowns, Polynomials, Quadratic Equations, Complex Numbers and Variations as part of the Algebra review.

As part of the Gemoetry review it covers Angles in Degrees and Right Triangle Trigonometry.

The material is written in an expository style with ample example problems, which helps in self learning. It also has exhaustive excersise problems after each sections with answers provided for all of them.